OL,7,FFalklands veteran Les Peake, now a
OL,8,Fbusinessman in , still lives with the
OL,9,Fmemory of the events of the morning of
OL,10,FJune 8, 1982, when the Sir Galahad, a
OL,11,FRoyal Fleet Auxiliary (RFA) ship, was
OL,12,Fsunk by the Argentinian air force.
OL,14,FHe said: "The families and the boys
OL,15,Fwant the documents released so we know
OL,16,Fexactly what went on on that day and
OL,17,Fwhy we were left there as sitting
OL,18,Fducks costing so many lives."
